  - Combat-Action=Metanoia=‘Duo Sunt in Homine’
  - 859
By: John Smith the Platonist
---
A watchful observer of his own heart and life shall often hear the
voice of wisdom and the voice of folly speaking to him： he that hath
his eyes opened, may see both the visions of God falling upon him, and
discern the false and foolish fires of Satan that would draw away his
mind from God.
